# scatter plots general

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
# likes por d√≠a de la semana
boxplot(actividad$Likes ~ actividad$DayWeek, main = "Likes x d√≠a", xlab = "D√≠a (1=Lunes)", ylab = "Likes")
# alcance por d√≠a de la semana
boxplot(actividad$M.Reach ~ actividad$DayWeek, main = "Media Reach x d√≠a", xlab = "D√≠a (1=Lunes)", ylab = "Media Reach")

# ahora por objetivo
boxplot(actividad$Likes ~ actividad$Objective, main = "Likes x Objetivo", xlab = "Objetivos", ylab = "Likes")

Tablas de contigencias (variables categ√≥ricas)

# ocurrencias del n√∫mero de post¬¥s
table(actividad$M.Count)
## 
##  1  2  3 
## 81  2  3
# acumulados por d√≠a
for (i in 1:7) 
{
  cat("D√≠a ",i,"-> Posts:",sum(subset(actividad, DayWeek == i)$M.Count),
      ", Likes:",sum(subset(actividad, DayWeek == i)$Likes),
      ", Comments:",sum(subset(actividad, DayWeek == i)$Comments),"\n")
}
## D√≠a  1 -> Posts: 13 , Likes: 1360 , Comments: 2262

# an√°lisis por Objective
objetivos <- unique(actividad$Objective)
for (i in objetivos) 
{
  
  cat("Objetivo:",i,"-> Posts:",sum(subset(actividad, Objective == i)$M.Count),
      ", Likes:",sum(subset(actividad, Objective == i)$Likes),
      ", Comments:",sum(subset(actividad, Objective == i)$Comments),"\n")
}
